The validation of a given string as a valid IPv4 address should be possible for the system.The validation of a given string as a valid IPv6 address should be performed by the system.The condition for the system to determine the validity of a given string as an IP address of any type is that the string should not be a valid IP address.If the string passed as the parameter is a valid IPv4 address, the system should return "str_IPv4".If the string passed as the parameter is a valid IPv6 address, the system should return "str_IPv6".If the string passed as the parameter to the method is not a valid IP address of any type, the system should return the string "str_Neither".